SIMPLE: madrier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Madrier
<hw>Ma*drier"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from Sp.
<ets>madero</ets>, or Pg. <ets>madeiro</ets>, fr. Sp. <ets>madera</ets>
wood for building, timber, Pg. <ets>madeira</ets>, L. <ets>materia</ets>
stuff, materials, lumber. See <er>Matter</er>.]</ety> <def>A thick
plank, used for several mechanical purposes</def>;
<specif>especially:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A plank to receive the
mouth of a petard, with which it is applied to anything intended to be
broken down.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A plank or beam used for supporting
the earth in mines or fortifications.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madrigal</ent>⟦br⟧
